  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective hemolysis measurement campaign conducted across five flow-speed operating points on a benchtop blood analog loop. The campaign is described throughout the submission as a controlled experiment with defined inlet/outlet boundary conditions, fixed hematocrit, and replicated runs; the structured activity record, however, classifies the data-collection protocol as an observational study, since pump operating conditions were set by clinical perfusionist preference rather than by a randomized or fully controlled experimental design. This distinction is not surfaced in the narrative and the inference chain from requirement to evidence therefore carries a latent method-mismatch.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-controlled-experiment",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-rh-below-1",
