    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet their required levels at MRL 2. The benchtop hemolysis measurement campaign provides quantitative validation evidence across the full COU operating envelope, with mean RHI prediction error of 8.3 % well below the 15 % acceptance criterion. All five predicted RHI values are below 1.0 relative to the predicate device. Mesh sensitivity, code verification, and software QA factors are satisfied. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. The credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the intended use decision.",
